    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hey all, I checked and this is due to having `<InstantSearchNext>` with no InstantSearch widgets inside.\n\nWe assume there will always be some as all our documentation and examples have `<InstantSearch>` not in layout but on the page itself, with widgets inside. Technically we don't try to support having it in the layout.\n\nIn the meantime you could add a `useHits()` or some other hook to ensure you at least have a widget and it should work I believe. I'll try to debug this but it seems like a weird hydration problem that's somehow not raised by Next.js.",
